snippet.textDisplay: This is scary. I’ve been robbed before I had I think two people (drug addicts) break into my apartment while I was at work. I work in a club so I was home by 3am I lived alone and I was only 21 this was 2018 in November Black Friday morning after. I walked up to my door and realized it was open and my jaw dropped. I peeped inside and seen nobody but my apartment was clearly trashed my Christmas tree upside down and I seen my couch flipped. I ran to my car crying called 911 in fear and locked my car doors. The police came and once inside I realized they stole my whole entire wardrobe, panties included, shoes gone, literally everything gone, stole a couple purses, a pair of diamond earrings, and that was it? They didn’t take much but I realized now I had no clothes or anything to wear really at all. My cat was missing too and I was in tears completely devastated over my kitty. I found my cat under the mattress eventually shaking.😭 her litter box was flipped they destroyed my apartment like ripped things open it looked crazy and I had to move break my lease. Which now I owe money on top of that they got away with it but I know who did it because a screen shot kinda gave it away how ever the police don’t have enough evidence to say it was them. It was a couple on drugs and it was clear they wanted money. They looked high and dry in my apartment and left it a mess taking my whole wardrobe probably out of anger. They kicked my door in and damaged my windows. It was a nightmare.......... and I wonder all the time what they would’ve done to me considering I was coming home alone at 3am and probably missed them by 20 mins........ I feel like they would’ve killed me. I also had money on me from the night of work😣 they would’ve definitely robbed me and killed me. Thankfully I didn’t leave no money or cards at my home when I left that night. You could tell these people were pissed they broke into my place and realized that I didn’t really have shit to take. Needless to say it was the most crazy thing I’ve ever had happen....... the feeling of a intruder invading your privacy is scary as fuck. It’s a very violating feeling.......

snippet.textDisplay:
First we had the biographical Jeffree Star YouTube series Shane Dawson produced a couple years ago, which was followed by the Conspiracy palette docu-series and subsequent product release; FINALLY, enter the brand new "Shane Glossin" YouTube channel complete with its premiere video crediting "Shane Glossin" as the makeup artist.
HOW did Shane Dawson go from being YouTube's "every-man," a content creator of arguable intellectual substance, TO a cosmetic brand collaborator and self-styled makeup artist of questionable talent, all in the course of LESS THAN FIVE YEARS???
Everything about this "Shane Glossin" persona is unrealistic and seemingly influenced by his relationship with Jeffree Star! I hate to say this, but...
Shane Dawson presents himself to be the dare-I-say "lackey" to the narcissistic Jeffree Star's over-the-top media whore persona. Shane Dawson continues to play the role of a "poor schmuck" looking into the unbelievably gluttonous lifestyle of "rich boy" Jeffree Star from the periphery; does Dawson think he can continue to pull off the "poor boy stumbling through a rich boy's world" when he's also worth millions?!?!?! The people, the relationships, the events...fake, fake, fake!
Come on Shane, your viewers aren't that dumb....
OR MAYBE THEY ARE..LOL!!!
